3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the Look-Compute-Move cycles of the agents, which involves distributed computing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a protocol for solving the Complete Visibility problem, which involves designing algorithms for coordinating the movements of the agents. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with controlling the movements of the agents to achieve a specific goal, which is a typical topic in the field of systems and control.
